      "text": [
        " يَوْمَيْنِ فَلاٰ إِثْمَ عَلَيْهِ وَ مَنْ تَأَخَّرَ فَلاٰ إِثْمَ عَلَيْهِ ۝» قَالَ «يَرْجِعُ مَغْفُوراً لاَ ذَنْبَ لَهُ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2201 - Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) was asked about the words of Allah (swt), Mighty and Majestic: \"Then whoever hastens to leave in two days, there is no sin upon him; and whoever delays, there is no sin upon him\" (Surah Al-Baqarah, 2:203).\nImam (as) said: \"They return forgiven, with no sin upon them.\""
        ]
      }
    },
